5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to motor vehicle license plates; to add
10 Section 32-6-354 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to establish a
11 combat action special license plate; and to provide criminal
12 penalties for falsely obtaining such a license plate.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Section 32-6-354 is added to the Code of
15 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
16 §32-6-354
17 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the
18 contrary, a distinctive license plate category is established
19 for motor vehicle owners who served in a component of the
20 United States Armed Forces and received the Combat Action
21 Ribbon, Combat Infantry Badge, Combat Action Badge, Combat
22 Medical Badge, Combat Action Medal, or Air Force Combat Action
23 Medal. The distinctive license plates shall be issued,
24 printed, and processed in the same manner as other distinctive
25 tags as provided in this chapter. An eligible U.S. service
26 member may apply to the judge of probate or other county
27 license plate issuing official in his or her county of
28 residence and present to the official one of the following as
Page 1

residence and present to the official one of the following as
HB107 Engrossed
29 proof of eligibility:
30 (1) A DD Form 214 stating that the service member
31 served in a combat theater and received awards or ribbons that
32 indicate combat experience.
33 (2) A copy of the certificate that accompanied the
34 service medal or ribbon signifying the participation of the
35 service member in the combat action.
36 (3) The Combat Action Ribbon, Combat Infantry Badge,
37 Combat Action Badge, Combat Medical Badge, Combat Action
38 Medal, or Air Force Combat Action Medal.
39 (b) Upon a service member presenting satisfactory proof
40 to the county license plate issuing official of his or her
41 combat experience, the service member shall be issued the
42 requested number of distinctive license plates upon the
43 payment of the regular license fee for the plates, as provided
44 by law, and payment of the additional fee of three dollars
45 ($3) for each plate issued. The service member shall pay the
46 additional fee for each license plate issued thereafter. In
47 those years in which the decal is issued, the service member
48 shall pay the regular license fee for tags as provided by law.
49 The distinctive license plates shall be used only upon and for
50 personally owned, private passenger vehicles, including
51 station wagons and pickup trucks, registered in the name of
52 the service member applying, and when issued to the applicant
53 shall be used upon the vehicle for which issued in lieu of the
54 standard license plates normally issued for the vehicle. The
55 distinctive license plates authorized by this section shall be
56 as follows:
Page 2

as follows:
HB107 Engrossed
57 (1) Combat Action Ribbon designated by either:
58 a. United States Marine Corps, "Emblem of the United
59 States Marine Corps";
60 b. United States Navy, "Emblem of the United States
61 Navy"; or
62 c. Coast Guard, "Seal of the United States Coast
63 Guard."
64 (2) Combat Infantryman Badge designated with the U.S.
65 Army service mark, "Army Military service mark."
66 (3) Combat Action Badge designated with the U.S. Army
67 service mark, "Army Military service mark," or vis-a-vis the
68 alternate, "Combat Medical Badge".
69 (4) Air Force Combat Action Medal, United States Space
70 Force Combat Action Medal designated by either:
71 a. U.S. Air Force, "Emblem of the United States Air
72 Force"; or
73 b. U.S. Space Force Delta logo, "U.S. Space Force."
74 (c) The designation shall be placed to the left of the
75 plate identification number space and underneath the proper
76 branch insignia logo for each respective award or medal.
77 (d) The plate shall bear in bold print at the center
78 bottom of the plate under the numbering in bright white the
79 term "COMBAT VETERAN."
80 (e) The distinctive plate may not be personalized.
81 (f) The distinctive license plate may not be
82 transferred between motor vehicle owners and shall be subject
83 to the same provisions of law related to the transferring of
84 distinctive motor vehicle license plates provided in Section
Page 3

distinctive motor vehicle license plates provided in Section
HB107 Engrossed
85 32-6-154 or as otherwise provided by law or rule of the
86 Department of Revenue.
87 (g) Any individual who is proven to have falsely
88 obtained or falsely certified an individual to obtain a combat
89 action distinctive license plate issued under this section
90 shall be guilty of a Class C misdemeanor.
91 Section 2. This act shall become effective on January
92 1, 2027.
